parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and rust of the frame can lead to structural failure, causing the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: corrosion of the rear cross member
severe rusting of the entire undercarriage and subframe
and failure of the fuel tank strap.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of corrosion protection measures can lead to accelerated corrosion of the frame, resulting in structural failure and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: and failure of previous repairs to address corrosion issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to notify owners of recalls can lead to delays in addressing safety issues, potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: and lack of assistance from manufacturers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the frame can lead to structural failure, causing the vehicle to collapse or lose control, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: especially in the rear leaf spring area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball joints can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower ball joint can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
